Eryx, Erycis, in.: a mountain and town on the west coast of Sicily, near Drepanum. It was famous for its temple of Aphrodite. The mountain was seized by the Romans at the close of the First Punic War, and here they were blockaded by Hamilcar for many months. A second Roman force then bloekaded Hamilcar in his turn, but he held the position until the battle of the Aegates Insulae eut off his communications by sea, and he was forced to surrender (10).
